com.pump.plaf

Class DecoratedPanelUI.Renderer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pump.plaf.DecoratedPanelUI.Renderer
  • Enclosing class:
    DecoratedPanelUI

    public static class DecoratedPanelUI.Renderer
extends java.lang.Object
    This is used by both the DecoratedPanelUI.Border and the DecoratedPanelUI to render all the attributes.

    You can override some methods to provide unique looks. For example by override the paintBody(Graphics2D, Component, Map) method you can fill the body with a texture paint to resemble brushed metal (which makes the attributes DecoratedPanelUI.COLOR_TOP and DecoratedPanelUI.COLOR_BOTTOM irrelevant). If customizing renderers via subclasses becomes a common pattern then this class should be refactored to somehow take that into account.

      • paint

        public void paint(java.awt.Graphics2D g,
                  java.awt.Component c,
                  java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> attributes)
        Paints everything in this renderer, after updating the body/glaze shapes. Specifically this invokes the paint methods in this order:
        1. paintDropShadow(Graphics2D, Component, Map)
        2. paintBody(Graphics2D, Component, Map)
        3. paintBevels(Graphics2D, Component, Map)
        4. paintGlaze(Graphics2D, Component, Map)
        5. paintBorder(Graphics2D, Component, Map)
        Parameters:
        g - the graphics to paint to.
        c - the component being rendered.
        attributes - the available attributes, note some may be missing.
